# Scientific Calculator

I'll create a beautiful, functional scientific calculator in a single HTML file with all the requested features. The calculator will support basic operations, parentheses, square root, and power functions.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Scientific Calculator</title>
    <style>
        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
        }
        
        body {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            min-height: 100vh;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a2a6c, #b21f1f, #1a2a6c);
            padding: 20px;
        }
        
        .calculator {
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 400px;
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
            backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
            border-radius: 20px;
            box-shadow: 0 15px 35px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
            overflow: hidden;
            border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
        }
        
        .display {
            padding: 25px 20px;
            background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
            text-align: right;
            border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
        }
        
        .expression {
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
            min-height: 30px;
            overflow: hidden;
            text-overflow: ellipsis;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }
        
        .result {
            font-size: 2.5rem;
            font-weight: 500;
            color: white;
            min-height: 50px;
            overflow: hidden;
            text-overflow: ellipsis;
        }
        
        .buttons {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(5, 1fr);
            gap: 1px;
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
        }
        
        button {
            border: none;
            outline: none;
            background: rgba(30, 30, 40, 0.8);
            color: white;
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            padding: 20px 10px;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: all 0.2s ease;
            position: relative;
            overflow: hidden;
        }
        
        button:hover {
            background: rgba(50, 50, 70, 0.9);
            transform: translateY(-2px);
        }
        
        button:active {
            transform: translateY(1px);
        }
        
        .operator {
            background: rgba(40, 40, 60, 0.8);
            font-weight: bold;
        }
        
        .operator:hover {
            background: rgba(60, 60, 90, 0.9);
        }
        
        .equals {
            background: linear-gradient(45deg, #ff8a00, #e52e71);
            grid-column: span 2;
        }
        
        .equals:hover {
            background: linear-gradient(45deg, #ff9a2e, #f53e81);
        }
        
        .clear {
            background: rgba(200, 50, 50, 0.7);
        }
        
        .clear:hover {
            background: rgba(220, 70, 70, 0.8);
        }
        
        .function {
            background: rgba(50, 150, 150, 0.7);
        }
        
        .function:hover {
            background: rgba(70, 170, 170, 0.8);
        }
        
        .footer {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 15px;
            color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
        }
        
        @media (max-width: 480px) {
            .calculator {
                max-width: 100%;
            }
            
            button {
                padding: 18px 5px;
                font-size: 1rem;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="calculator">
        <div class="display">
            <div class="expression" id="expression"></div>
            <div class="result" id="result">0</div>
        </div>
        <div class="buttons">
            <button class="clear" onclick="clearAll()">C</button>
            <button class="clear" onclick="backspace()">⌫</button>
            <button class="function" onclick="appendToExpression('(')">(</button>
            <button class="function" onclick="appendToExpression(')')">)</button>
            <button class="function" onclick="appendToExpression('sqrt(')">√</button>
            
            <button class="function" onclick="appendToExpression('^')">x^y</button>
            <button class="function" onclick="appendToExpression('sin(')">sin</button>
            <button class="function" onclick="appendToExpression('cos(')">cos</button>
            <button class="function" onclick="appendToExpression('tan(')">tan</button>
            <button class="function" onclick="appendToExpression('log(')">log</button>
            
            <button onclick="appendToExpression('7')">7</button>
            <button onclick="appendToExpression('8')">8</button>
            <button onclick="appendToExpression('9')">9</button>
            <button class="operator" onclick="appendToExpression('/')">/</button>
            <button class="operator" onclick="appendToExpression('*')">×</button>
            
            <button onclick="appendToExpression('4')">4</button>
            <button onclick="appendToExpression('5')">5</button>
            <button onclick="appendToExpression('6')">6</button>
            <button class="operator" onclick="appendToExpression('-')">-</button>
            <button class="operator" onclick="appendToExpression('+')">+</button>
            
            <button onclick="appendToExpression('1')">1</button>
            <button onclick="appendToExpression('2')">2</button>
            <button onclick="appendToExpression('3')">3</button>
            <button class="operator" onclick="appendToExpression('(')">(</button>
            <button class="operator" onclick="appendToExpression(')')">)</button>
            
            <button onclick="appendToExpression('0')">0</button>
            <button onclick="appendToExpression('.')">.</button>
            <button class="operator" onclick="appendToExpression('Math.PI')">π</button>
            <button class="operator" onclick="appendToExpression('Math.E')">e</button>
            <button class="equals" onclick="calculate()">=</button>
        </div>
        <div class="footer">
            Scientific Calculator | Supports +, -, *, /, parentheses, sqrt, power
        </div>
    </div>

    <script>
        let expression = '';
        const expressionElement = document.getElementById('expression');
        const resultElement = document.getElementById('result');
        
        function appendToExpression(value) {
            expression += value;
            updateDisplay();
        }
        
        function clearAll() {
            expression = '';
            updateDisplay();
        }
        
        function backspace() {
            expression = expression.slice(0, -1);
            updateDisplay();
        }
        
        function updateDisplay() {
            expressionElement.textContent = expression;
            if (expression === '') {
                resultElement.textContent = '0';
            } else {
                resultElement.textContent = evaluateExpression(expression);
            }
        }
        
        function evaluateExpression(expr) {
            try {
                // Replace mathematical functions and constants
                expr = expr.replace(/sqrt\(/g, 'Math.sqrt(');
                expr = expr.replace(/sin\(/g, 'Math.sin(');
                expr = expr.replace(/cos\(/g, 'Math.cos(');
                expr = expr.replace(/tan\(/g, 'Math.tan(');
                expr = expr.replace(/log\(/g, 'Math.log10(');
                expr = expr.replace(/\^/g, '**');
                expr = expr.replace(/π/g, 'Math.PI');
                expr = expr.replace(/e/g, 'Math.E');
                
                // Evaluate the expression
                const result = eval(expr);
                
                // Format the result
                if (Number.isInteger(result)) {
                    return result.toString();
                } else {
                    return parseFloat(result.toFixed(10)).toString();
                }
            } catch (error) {
                return 'Error';
            }
        }
        
        function calculate() {
            if (expression === '') return;
            
            try {
                // Replace mathematical functions and constants
                let expr = expression;
                expr = expr.replace(/sqrt\(/g, 'Math.sqrt(');
                expr = expr.replace(/sin\(/g, 'Math.sin(');
                expr = expr.replace(/cos\(/g, 'Math.cos(');
                expr = expr.replace(/tan\(/g, 'Math.tan(');
                expr = expr.replace(/log\(/g, 'Math.log10(');
                expr = expr.replace(/\^/g, '**');
                expr = expr.replace(/π/g, 'Math.PI');
                expr = expr.replace(/e/g, 'Math.E');
                
                const result = eval(expr);
                
                // Format the result
                if (Number.isInteger(result)) {
                    expression = result.toString();
                } else {
                    expression = parseFloat(result.toFixed(10)).toString();
                }
                
                updateDisplay();
            } catch (error) {
                expression = 'Error';
                updateDisplay();
            }
        }
        
        // Initialize display
        updateDisplay();
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

## Features of this Scientific Calculator:

1. **Beautiful Design**:
   - Gradient background with glass-morphism effect
   - Responsive layout that works on all devices
   - Modern color scheme with visual feedback on button presses
   - Clean typography and spacing

2. **Full Functionality**:
   - Basic operations: +, -, *, /
   - Parentheses support for complex expressions
   - Square root function (sqrt)
   - Power function (x^y)
   - Trigonometric functions: sin, cos, tan
   - Logarithmic function (log)
   - Constants: π (pi) and e
   - Clear (C) and backspace (⌫) buttons

3. **User Experience**:
   - Shows both the expression and result
   - Real-time calculation as you type
   - Error handling for invalid expressions
   - Responsive buttons with hover and active states
   - Clear visual hierarchy

Simply copy and paste this code into an HTML file and open it in any modern browser to use the calculator.
